theorem Topology.closure_frontier_eq_closure_diff_self_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    closure (frontier A) = closure A \ A := by
  -- First, rewrite `frontier A` in terms of `closure A` and `A`,
  -- using the fact that `A` is open.
  have hFront : frontier A = closure A \ A := by
    simpa [hA.interior_eq] using
      (Topology.frontier_eq_closure_diff_self_of_isOpen (A := A) hA)
  -- Since the frontier is a closed set, its closure is itself.
  have hClosFront : closure (frontier A) = frontier A :=
    Topology.closure_frontier_eq_frontier (A := A)
  -- Combine the two equalities to obtain the desired statement.
  simpa [hClosFront, hFront]

@[simp] theorem Topology.closure_diff_self_eq_self_of_isOpen
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    closure (closure A \ A) = closure A \ A := by
  -- First, show that `closure A \ A` is a closed set.
  have hClosed : IsClosed (closure A \ A) := by
    -- `closure A` is closed.
    have h₁ : IsClosed (closure A) := isClosed_closure
    -- The complement of an open set is closed.
    have h₂ : IsClosed ((A : Set X)ᶜ) := hA.isOpen_compl
    -- Rewrite the set difference as an intersection to combine the two facts.
    have : closure A \ A = closure A ∩ Aᶜ := by
      simp [Set.diff_eq, Set.inter_comm, Set.inter_left_comm]
    -- The intersection of two closed sets is closed.
    simpa [this] using h₁.inter h₂
  -- The closure of a closed set is the set itself.
  simpa [hClosed.closure_eq]

theorem Topology.frontier_eq_closure_inter_compl_of_isOpen' {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hA : IsOpen A) :
    frontier A = closure A ∩ Aᶜ := by
  have h := Topology.frontier_eq_closure_diff_self_of_isOpen (A := A) hA
  simpa [Set.diff_eq] using h
